Cook,<br><br>
Your recent posting prompted me to re-read Thread 107.  Ronald Allan Moore is one of those men you could never forget and now neither can I.  Thank you for reminding me to focus on the reason I choose to remember.<br><br>
I look at now at one of the few treasures on my desk.  A gift from a man on my birthday who cared, but had no way to buy a gift.  Handed to me with a smile was a rock.  Scratched into its surface was ROCK  captured on 23 Nov. 1968.  It meant something to him and now it means everything to me.  I buried him in 1969.  Gone, but never forgotten<br><br>
I look forward to the many stories You have to tell.  When you book hits the stands you can count on one copy sold.<br><br>
Honor to those who served
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


